{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:51:32.537489+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 158, "prompt_tokens": 6024, "total_tokens": 6182, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 94, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 5824}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "83b36ae987a44c4683f6d9f320571a83", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead82-be25-7a72-bc2d-8472e9f70f4a-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "get_file_contents", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "path": "README.md", "ref": "main", "repo": "T10_R01_C03_A03"}, "id": "call_e44f41541af84dfe82fc5dcd", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 6024, "output_tokens": 158, "total_tokens": 6182, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 5824}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 94}}}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:51:33.148182+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:PqvMqK | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: dd8f230ebcee1ed2c87953be052ec8d2681c21fc)", "id": "lc_5e275dd3-8e93-455c-93aa-bc8c5b8274a6"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:PqvMqK | # vidpack — profile-driven FFmpeg wrapper\n| MCP:PqvMqK | \n| MCP:PqvMqK | `vidpack` is a small Python CLI that runs FFmpeg using named profiles defined\n| MCP:PqvMqK | in `profiles.toml`. The goal is to avoid memorizing long ffmpeg flag strings\n| MCP:PqvMqK | for routine encoding jobs.\n| MCP:PqvMqK | \n| MCP:PqvMqK | FFmpeg is **not** bundled. `vidpack` expects `ffmpeg` (and `ffprobe`, where\n| MCP:PqvMqK | relevant) to be available on `PATH`.\n| MCP:PqvMqK | \n| MCP:PqvMqK | ## Install\n| MCP:PqvMqK | \n| MCP:PqvMqK | ```\n| MCP:PqvMqK | pip install -e .\n| MCP:PqvMqK | ```\n| MCP:PqvMqK | \n| MCP:PqvMqK | This registers the `vidpack` command.\n| MCP:PqvMqK | \n| MCP:PqvMqK | ## Profiles\n| MCP:PqvMqK | \n| MCP:PqvMqK | The default `profiles.toml` ships three profiles:\n| MCP:PqvMqK | \n| MCP:PqvMqK | | Profile   | Container | Video codec | Audio codec | Notes                       |\n| MCP:PqvMqK | |-----------|-----------|-------------|-------------|-----------------------------|\n| MCP:PqvMqK | | `web`     | mp4       | libx264     | aac         | 720p, target bitrate 2 Mbps |\n| MCP:PqvMqK | | `archive` | mkv       | libx265     | flac        | source resolution, CRF 18   |\n| MCP:PqvMqK | | `gif`     | gif       | (palette)   | (none)      | 480p wide, 12 fps           |\n| MCP:PqvMqK | \n| MCP:PqvMqK | Edit `profiles.toml` to customize or add profiles.\n| MCP:PqvMqK | \n| MCP:PqvMqK | ## Usage\n| MCP:PqvMqK | \n| MCP:PqvMqK | ```\n| MCP:PqvMqK | vidpack <profile> <input> [-o OUTPUT] [--dry-run]\n| MCP:PqvMqK | ```\n| MCP:PqvMqK | \n| MCP:PqvMqK | If `-o` is omitted, the output filename is derived from the input by\n| MCP:PqvMqK | replacing the extension with the profile's container extension.\n| MCP:PqvMqK | \n| MCP:PqvMqK | `--dry-run` prints the ffmpeg command vidpack would run, without executing it.\n| MCP:PqvMqK | \n| MCP:PqvMqK | By default, vidpack will **not** overwrite an existing output file; it exits\n| MCP:PqvMqK | with an error. Delete the output manually or pass a different `-o`.\n| MCP:PqvMqK | \n| MCP:PqvMqK | ## Examples\n| MCP:PqvMqK | \n| MCP:PqvMqK | ```\n| MCP:PqvMqK | # Re-encode an mp4 for web at 720p\n| MCP:PqvMqK | vidpack web input.mov -o talk.mp4\n| MCP:PqvMqK | \n| MCP:PqvMqK | # Lossless-ish archive copy\n| MCP:PqvMqK | vidpack archive input.mov\n| MCP:PqvMqK | \n| MCP:PqvMqK | # Preview the ffmpeg command for the gif profile without running it\n| MCP:PqvMqK | vidpack gif clip.mp4 --dry-run\n| MCP:PqvMqK | ```\n| MCP:PqvMqK | \n| MCP:PqvMqK | ## License\n| MCP:PqvMqK | \n| MCP:PqvMqK | MIT", "id": "lc_24dbec59-fbde-4a6c-8ef8-f820acf4eb28"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "05b0199f-c0b3-46f9-9c4f-84e72c5c2007", "tool_call_id": "call_e44f41541af84dfe82fc5dcd", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
