{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:52:19.152796+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "The token doesn't have permission to update issue state/labels. Let me add a comment summarizing the triage findings instead.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 322, "prompt_tokens": 10705, "total_tokens": 11027, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 23, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 10112}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "98e8698c5e0a4429b65701f64d335e63", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead83-5e6a-7300-a523-8b0e2b2a3613-0", "tool_calls": [{"name": "add_issue_comment", "args": {"owner": "rpnr-bench", "repo": "T10_R01_C03_A03", "issue_number": 1, "body": "Triage review completed. I've confirmed against the current codebase that this is **working as designed** and recommend closing as `wontfix`:\n\n1. **`runner.py` (line ~17)** confirms the gif profile uses a single-pass `-vf fps=...,scale=...:flags=lanczos` filter — no two-pass `palettegen`/`paletteuse` pipeline.\n2. **`profiles.toml`** already documents this explicitly: *\"the gif profile currently uses a single-pass palette generation, which is convenient but produces noticeably worse quality than a proper two-pass palettegen / paletteuse pipeline.\"*\n3. The existing comment on this issue from the codecs subteam already laid out the rationale (intentional speed tradeoff, named `gif` not `gif-hq`, would be a regression for internal users who prefer speed).\n\nSince I don't have the token permissions to apply the `wontfix` label or close the issue directly, I'm leaving this comment for a maintainer to action."}, "id": "call_539b7b7c571e498f842fb331", "type": "tool_call"}], "i